      "acceptanceCriteria": "Software used for simulation is under version control with documented test suite and release notes meeting Gradation 2 requirements.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent 2022 R2 was used under an ISO 9001-compliant QMS. Version control records, regression test results, and release notes are on file. Achieved level meets the required level for MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver accuracy confirmed via method of manufactured solutions or equivalent benchmark with documented order-of-accuracy results.",
      "rationale": "Method of manufactured solutions applied to the incompressible Navier-Stokes solver confirmed second-order spatial accuracy. Benchmark results are archived and traceable to the simulation package."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) or Richardson extrapolation applied; discretization error quantified and shown to be below 5% for primary QoI.",
      "rationale": "A three-level mesh refinement study was performed. Richardson extrapolation yielded a GCI of 2.1% for the peak shear stress QoI on the finest mesh. The achieved level exceeds the MRL 2 requirement, providing additional confidence in spatial accuracy."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions are documented and sufficiently match the simulation boundary conditions to support meaningful comparison.",
      "rationale": "FDA bench-top experiments were conducted at the same five flow-rate and rotational-speed combinations used in the CFD model. Fluid temperature, hematocrit, and anticoagulation protocol were documented and replicated in simulation boundary conditions."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric defined; predicted and measured hemolysis index values compared with documented agreement criterion.",
      "rationale": "The normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) and relative hemolysis index (RH) were computed for all five operating points. Predicted RH values ranged from 0.72 to 0.91, all below the acceptance threshold of 1.0, with mean absolute error of 8.3% relative to experimental measurements."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs used in validation directly correspond to the hemolysis metrics used in the regulatory decision.",
      "rationale": "The primary QoI is the relative hemolysis index RH, which is the exact metric specified in the COU acceptance criterion. Secondary QoIs include volume-averaged shear stress and exposure time, which feed directly into the power-law hemolysis damage model."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments performed on a device geometrically and operationally representative of the COU device under CPB conditions.",
      "rationale": "Validation used the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry operated across the same flow-speed envelope as the COU. Blood analog fluid properties and pump operating pressures are consistent with clinical CPB conditions, supporting direct applicability of validation evidence to the COU."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2 when discretization error has been separately assessed.",
      "rationale": "Solver iterative convergence was monitored via residual norms (all below 1e-5) and mass-balance checks. Formal solver error quantification beyond residual monitoring is not required at MRL 2 given the discretization error assessment already performed."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2 for this COU.",
      "rationale": "Use error assessment is not required at Model Risk Level 2 for this context of use. Simulation setup was reviewed by a second analyst as a procedural safeguard, but formal use-error quantification was not performed."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The governing equations and constitutive models selected are appropriate for the flow regime and hemolysis prediction in a centrifugal blood pump.",
      "rationale": "The Reynolds-averaged Navier-Stokes equations with the SST k-omega turbulence closure were selected based on published benchmarks for rotating blood-contacting devices. The Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law hemolysis model was applied consistently with prior FDA validation studies, confirming suitability of the model form for this COU."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Key model inputs (fluid properties, boundary conditions, geometry) are documented with sources and uncertainty ranges where applicable.",
      "rationale": "Blood analog viscosity (3.5 mPa·s), density (1060 kg/m³), pump geometry (nominal CAD), inlet flow rates, and rotational speeds are fully documented with traceability to experimental protocols. Uncertainty in fluid viscosity (±5%) was propagated through a sensitivity study confirming minimal impact on RH predictions."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2 for this COU.",
      "rationale": "Formal characterization of test sample variability is not required at MRL 2. The FDA experimental dataset used for validation employed standardized bovine blood preparations with documented hematocrit and anticoagulant protocol, which is sufficient for this assessment level."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2 for this COU.",
      "rationale": "Equivalency of input parameters between the validation experiment and the COU is addressed qualitatively through the model inputs and test conditions factors. A formal equivalency mapping is not required at MRL 2 and has not been performed."
    }
  ],
  "hasWeakener": [],
  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/morrison-cou1-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The CFD model for hemolysis prediction in the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump is accepted as credible for COU1. All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels for Model Risk Level 2: software quality assurance is maintained under an ISO 9001-compliant QMS, numerical code verification confirms second-order solver accuracy, discretization error is quantified at 2.1% GCI, test conditions are documented and matched to simulation boundary conditions, output comparison yields a mean absolute error of 8.3% with all RH predictions below the 1.0 acceptance threshold, quantities of interest directly correspond to the regulatory hemolysis metric, and validation activities were performed on a geometrically and operationally representative device under CPB conditions. The six remaining factors are not assessed, which is consistent with the requirements for MRL 2. The totality of positive evidence across all assessed factors demonstrates that the model is fit for the intended purpose of identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device, and the decision to accept the simulation results for regulatory submission is fully supported.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
  },
